evidence.notes: Initiates goal-setting structure (SMART goals) and proactively asks user to choose a target area (activity/nutrition/sleep) despite user only greeting.
Proposes a concrete, manageable activity approach (short breaks/walks) and asks user to choose between minutes vs. exercises to shape the plan.
Directly elicits missing SMART elements (frequency: days/week) and asks about motivation/reward to support adherence.
Makes the goal more time-bound by proposing a 2-week timeframe and a check-in, advancing the SMART structure.
Transitions to the next agenda item by asking which domain to address next (sleep vs. nutrition).
User requested to discuss nutrition; assistant narrows focus by offering options (evening meal planning vs other aspect), but this is largely prompted by the user’s request.
User asks if junk food dinners are okay/needs change; assistant cautions and offers structured next directions (healthier versions vs plan easy dinners), but within the requested advice.

User states constraint (too tired); assistant proactively proposes specific quick dinner options and asks user to choose a path (one meal vs several), moving planning forward without a direct user question.
Answers the time estimate (prompted) and adds an unprompted feasibility check ('How does that fit with your evening routine?') to surface barriers.
Turns the idea into a more concrete plan by suggesting specific days (Tue/Thu) and a reward, then asks for agreement.
Summarizes and formalizes the dinner SMART plan (days, <30 min, reward) and explicitly asks for confirmation/adjustments.
After setting dinner plan, proactively offers to shift focus to another domain (sleep/activity) and asks which is most relevant.
Mostly reassurance and open-ended invitation to return later; no concrete next step, missing element check, or commitment detail added.
Closing/thanks only; does not advance the plan.

session_summary.notes: Assistant frequently drove the session forward by eliciting SMART details (frequency/timeframe), proposing concrete options, and confirming plans. Lower-proactivity moments were primarily prompted nutrition advice turns and the final closing turns with no further planning.
